    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="94"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/1445a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-01T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1727. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1328. For your confidential information. Supplementing Department’s 1648,
                    September 27, 3 p.m., our 1282. Swedish sailing vessels will be permitted to
                    traverse the danger zone <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> to Sweden provided (1)
                    that if any such vessel carry any quantity of petroleum or its by-products or
                    foodstuffs as cargo, such petroleum and its by-products and foodstuffs must be
                    so stowed in the hold of the vessel beneath cargo of a different nature as to
                    make it manifestly difficult for any submarine to remove such petroleum or its
                    by-products or foodstuffs, and provided (2) that no such vessel will be
                    permitted to sail with any quantity of brass, copper, or other similar metals as
                    such. Repeat to <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_OWH1">Owen</persName> as
                    confidential information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
